26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_mc_base.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:34 riastradh Exp $");

29#include "priv.h"
30
31#include <core/option.h>
32
33void
34nvkm_mc_unk260(struct nvkm_mc *mc, u32 data)
35{
36 if (mc->func->unk260)
37 mc->func->unk260(mc, data);
38}
39
40void
41nvkm_mc_intr_unarm(struct nvkm_mc *mc)
42{
43 return mc->func->intr_unarm(mc);
44}
45
46void
47nvkm_mc_intr_rearm(struct nvkm_mc *mc)
48{
49 return mc->func->intr_rearm(mc);
50}
51
52static u32
53nvkm_mc_intr_mask(struct nvkm_mc *mc)
54{
55 u32 intr = mc->func->intr_mask(mc);
56 if (WARN_ON_ONCE(intr == 0xffffffff))
57 intr = 0; /* likely fallen off the bus */
58 return intr;
59}
60
61void
62nvkm_mc_intr(struct nvkm_mc *mc, bool *handled)
63{
64 struct nvkm_device *device = mc->subdev.device;
65 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev;
66 const struct nvkm_mc_intr *map = mc->func->intr;
67 u32 stat, intr;
68
69 stat = intr = nvkm_mc_intr_mask(mc);
70 while (map->stat) {
71 if (intr & map->stat) {
72 subdev = nvkm_device_subdev(device, map->unit);
73 if (subdev)
74 nvkm_subdev_intr(subdev);
75 stat &= ~map->stat;
76 }
77 map++;
78 }
79
80 if (stat)
81 nvkm_error(&mc->subdev, "intr %08x\n", stat);
82 *handled = intr != 0;
83}
84
85static int
86nvkm_mc_fini(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev, bool suspend)
87{
88 struct nvkm_mc *mc = nvkm_mc(subdev);
89 nvkm_mc_intr_unarm(mc);
90 return 0;
91}
92
93static int
94nvkm_mc_init(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
95{
96 struct nvkm_mc *mc = nvkm_mc(subdev);
97 if (mc->func->init)
98 mc->func->init(mc);
99 nvkm_mc_intr_rearm(mc);
100 return 0;
101}
102
103static void *
104nvkm_mc_dtor(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
105{
106 return nvkm_mc(subdev);
107}
108
109static const struct nvkm_subdev_func
110nvkm_mc = {
111 .dtor = nvkm_mc_dtor,
112 .init = nvkm_mc_init,
113 .fini = nvkm_mc_fini,
114};
115
116int
117nvkm_mc_new_(const struct nvkm_mc_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
118 int index, struct nvkm_mc **pmc)
119{
120 struct nvkm_mc *mc;
121
122 if (!(mc = *pmc = kzalloc(sizeof(*mc), GFP_KERNEL)))
123 return -ENOMEM;
124
125 nvkm_subdev_ctor(&nvkm_mc, device, index, 0, &mc->subdev);
126 mc->func = func;
127 return 0;
128}
